{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"512e97b5-2cdf-4045-8332-7656d142b7cb","content":"Analyzing .dmp files is outside the scope of the `dump-collect` skill (which only covers **collecting** dumps). Here's a quick guide for analysis:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze <your-file>.dmp\n```\nUseful SOS commands inside the session:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack\n- `pe` — print last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all threads\n\n**Using lldb (Linux)**:\n```bash\nlldb --core <your-file>.dmp\nplugin load libsosplugin.so\nsos clrstack\nsos pe\n```\n\n**Using WinDbg (Windows)**:\nOpen the dump, load SOS (`.loadby sos coreclr`), then run `!pe` and `!clrstack`.\n\nStart with `pe` (print exception) — it usually points straight to the crash cause. Want help with any of these steps?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"43882f55-d6a1-4fb2-9269-4a648d2e5ccd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description says it's for **collecting** crash dumps, and explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the skill doesn't apply here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":368,"requestId":"9423:634EC:185E39E:1BC29AD:69E82137"},"id":"6e3d5dc6-c63b-4f43-bfa0-e687249ad5e9","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:16:31.427Z","parentId":"ce9fcca3-5a9e-4264-93b3-3e295e3ac9be"}
